      "content": "This yellowing on the lower leaves, while the top ones are fine, is a classic sign of nitrogen deficiency in your tomatoes. Nitrogen is a crucial nutrient for leafy growth, and when it runs low, the plant pulls it from the oldest leaves first. To fix this, you should apply a balanced, nitrogen-rich fertilizer, or you can amend your soil with compost or aged manure to naturally boost its nutrient content.",
